  <brief_title>Predictive Factors of Response to Somatostatin Analogues in Acromegalic Patients With Persistent Disease Following Surgery</brief_title>
  <acronym>ESPORA</acronym>
  <official_title>Observational Study to Evaluate, in Acromegalic Patients With Disease Persistence After Surgery, Those Histopathologic, Clinical, Morphologic and Biochemical Factors Predictors of Hormonal Control Under Somatostatin Analogue Treatment</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Ipsen</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Ipsen</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to evaluate, in acromegalic patients with disease persistence
      after surgery who are treated with somatostatin analogues, the histopathological, clinical,
      morphological and biochemical factors which are predictive of hormonal control.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
